AP Clarifies Anthrax Overseas Story
-------------------------------------------
In an 20 Oct 2001 story about global anthrax fears, The Associated
Press quoted Argentina's health minister, Hector Lombardo, as
saying a Carnival cruise [line brochure from Miami tested positive for
anthrax spores. The Health Ministry has since said the mailing
promoted a Carnival cruise but that it did not know who was
responsible for the mailing. Miami-based Carnival Cruise Lines says it
did not send any promotional material directly to Argentina, but
Carnival's name did appear in a mailing by an independent distributor
promoting cruises and other products from various companies.
On Thursday [25 Oct 2001, Argentine health officials said the anthrax
spores found on the travel brochure were of a harmless strain, akin to
those used in anthrax vaccinations for livestock.
--
